tes.\n- \u0060fsharp_check_file_order\u0060: Checks F# project file order for dependencies.\n- \u0060list_dir\u0060: Lists files and folders.\n- \u0060search_web\u0060: Searches web using DuckDuckGo (no API key needed).\n- \u0060cache_get\u0060: Retrieves cache values.\n- \u0060search_memory\u0060: Searches TARS\u0027s long-term memory.\n- \u0060save_memory\u0060: Saves facts/beliefs to TARS\u0027s long-term memory.\n\n### Lessons Learned\n1. Successfully optimized the \u0060reverseList\u0060 function to reduce memory usage.\n2. Created a test suite for the \u0060showSemanticMessage\u0060 function in the \u0060DemoVisualizationTests.fs\u0060 file.\n3. Refactored the \u0060showTaskComplete\u0060 function in \u0060DemoVisualization.fs\u0060 to reduce code duplication.\n4. Patched a given code snippet in \u0027SortList.fs\u0027 by adding a new function \u0060countCharOccurrences\u0060.\n5. Defined an absolute value function in \u0060Program.fs\u0060.\n6. Replaced original code in \u0027reverseList.fs\u0027 with a new version.\n7. Modified the \u0060countCharOccurrences\u0060 function to handle case sensitivity.\n8. Wrote a function to count character occurrences in strings.\n\n### Critical Instructions\n1. Act autonomously without asking questions or refusing tasks.\n2. Use available tools for environment interactions.\n3. Ensure 100% test coverage and validate performance improvements.\n4. Provide final solutions as \u0027Tell\u0027 or \u0027Inform\u0027 performative actions.\u0022\n     Timestamp = 2025-12-28 8:39:52 AM\n     Metadata = map [] }]",
